        public ContractPeriod​(java.time.LocalDate start,
                      java.time.LocalDate end,
                      T contractID,
                      PlanBenefitPackageID planBenefitPackageID)
        Create a new contract period. Contract periods have a one month granularity so the supplied start and end are adjusted to the first day of the start month and last day of the end month.
        Parameters:
        start - the start of the contract period
        end - the end of the contract period
        contractID - the contract id
        planBenefitPackageID - the plan benefit package id

      • ContractPeriod

        public ContractPeriod​(java.time.LocalDate start,
                      java.time.LocalDate end,
                      T contractID,
                      RandomNumberGenerator rand)
        Create a new contract period. Contract periods have a one month granularity so the supplied start and end are adjusted to the first day of the start month and last day of the end month. A random plan benefit package ID is chosen
        Parameters:
        start - the start of the contract period
        end - the end of the contract period
        contractID - the contract id
        rand - source of randomness

        public boolean covers​(long timeStamp)
